==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Benne
<hw>Ben"ne</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Malay
<ets>bijen</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The name of two plants
(<spn>Sesamum orientale</spn> and <spn>Sesamum indicum</spn>),
originally Asiatic; -- also called <altname>oil plant</altname>. From
their seeds an oil is expressed, called <prod>benne oil</prod> or
<prod>sesame oil</prod>, used mostly for making soap. In the southern
United States the seeds are used in candy.</def> <altsp>[Also spelled
<asp>benni</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bennet</ent>⟦br⟧
